# Core contract (Rust crates)

Each `crates/extralife-<device>` implements `extralife_core::Device` and only
that. The trait is the whole seam — see `crates/extralife-core/src/lib.rs`.

## Rules

- **Deterministic.** Same ROM + same inputs ⇒ byte-identical framebuffer, every
  run. No wall-clock, no time-seeded RNG, no threads in the hot path.
- **Headless.** No screen, audio device, or event loop assumed. The harness
  drives `step_frame` and reads `framebuffer()`.
- **Plain data at the edge.** `framebuffer()` is always RGBA8888, row-major,
  length `screen().framebuffer_len()`. The WASM/JS boundary is a memory read.
- **`load_rom` fully resets.** Two loads = two clean runs.
- **`load_state` is atomic.** On `Err`, leave the core unchanged.
- **`save_state`/`load_state` round-trip** on the same core version.

## Layout per crate

```
crates/extralife-<device>/
  Cargo.toml        # depends on extralife-core.workspace = true
  src/lib.rs        # the Device impl + a #[cfg(test)] contract check
```

Keep `extralife-core` tiny. Adding a trait method touches every core — do it
only when a real device forces it, and give it a sane default so silent cores
(no audio yet) compile unchanged.
